<div class="text interview">
<h2><a href="mailto:afshin.ziaei@thalesgroup.com" target="_blank">Afshin Ziaei</a> is project coordinator</h2>
QUESTIONS &amp; ANSWERS
<p class="paragraph question">What do you want to achieve with this project?</p>
<p class="paragraph">SATURNE's objective is to proue the feasibility and inherent advantages of using wideband gap and RF-MEMS based technologies in Intelligent Micro Systems for future space ultra wideband systems.</p>
<p class="paragraph question">Why is this project important for Europe?</p>
<p class="paragraph">SATURNE technology will be used in future satellites. This technology will meet the demands from providers and operators for more flexibility and mass reduction, and consequently offer new services. SATURNE will also preserve EU independence in the sat¬ellite domain.</p>
<p class="paragraph question">How does your work benefit European citizens?</p>
<p class="paragraph">Multiband satellites will allow more users and services per satellite. This will reduce the number of satellites needed and then reduces the cost for the final user. Mastering this technol¬ogy in Europe will help keeping high¬tech employment in Europe.</p>
